Norilsk Nickel, VTB and Rosneft: Russian Equities Preview

-- B y   S t e p h e n   B i e r m a n
-- 
2011-04-20T21:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-20/norilsk-nickel-vtb-and-rosneft-russian-equities-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close.  The 30-stock Micex Index rose 1.6 percent to 1,783.38. The
dollar-denominated RTS Index was up 2.2 percent to 2,030.97.  OAO GMK Norilsk Nickel (GMKN RX): United Co. Rusal, a
shareholder in OAO GMK Norilsk Nickel, said the company’s deal
to sell 8 percent of its shares to Trafigura Beheer BV lacked
transparency. Shares in  Russia ’s largest mining company climbed
2.7 percent to 7,691 rubles in Moscow.  VTB Group (VTBR RX): Russia’s second-largest bank
recommended paying out 14 percent of its net profit measured to
Russian accounting standards or 6.07 billion rubles ($216
million) as dividends for 2010. The bank paid out the same
amount a year earlier. VTB shares rose 1.3 percent to 0.09399
rubles in Moscow.  Rosneft (ROSN RX): Crude oil rose the most in a month after
the U.S. Energy Department reported an unexpected decline in
crude supplies. Russia’s largest oil producer rose 1.8 percent
to 253.94 rubles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Bierman in Moscow 
